chunk_content: Locally-recognized laboratory mentorship programs Certification/Accreditation: Refers to accreditation or certification by a national, regional or internationally recognized accreditation body, such as College of American Pathologists (CAP), International Organization for Standardization (ISO) accreditation programs, regional accreditation bodies such as the South African National Accreditation System (SANAS), local certification bodies, or other approved accreditation organizations. A point-of-care testing site is assessed by a standardized set of criteria defined by an acceptable local, national, regional, or international organization. Accreditation or certification certificates are a formal recognition that a point-of-care site is competent to perform clinical testing. Point-of-care testing site accreditation or certification status must be current.
